  "notes": "Hungarian (Magyar). Uralic language with 14-vowel system (7 short + 7 long), vowel harmony, palatal stops /c, ɟ/, and rich agglutinative morphology. Referenced as adstrate for Romanian due to centuries of Transylvanian contact (Siptár & Törkenczy 2000).",
